Academic Affairs

The LSUA Office of Academic Affairs champions academic excellence, innovative teaching, and student success. Dedicated to cultivating a vibrant intellectual community, our office supports and empowers faculty, staff, and students through collaboration, integrity, and transparency.

Through shared governance and close partnership with the Faculty Senate and university leadership, LSUA ensures that academic programs remain rigorous, relevant, and responsive to the evolving needs of our community. The office facilitates clear communication, strategic planning, and continuous improvement across all academic initiatives.

Academic Colleges

College of Business

The LSUA College of Business equips students with practical skills in business and accounting while bolstering critical thinking, innovation, and leadership. With an emphasis on real-world application and professional development, graduates are prepared to thrive in today’s global marketplace.

Accounting & Finance
Management & Marketing

College of Health & Human Services

The LSUA College of Health & Human Services is dedicated to improving lives by preparing students for impactful careers in healthcare and education. Through hands-on training, community partnerships, and strong career placement support, graduates can enter the workforce ready to lead and serve with excellence.

Allied Health
School of Nursing
School of Education

College of Liberal Arts

The LSUA College of Liberal Arts empowers students to think critically, communicate effectively, and engage creatively with the world. Offering adaptable degree pathways and personalized support, the college prepares graduates for meaningful careers while building fundamental skills for lifelong success.

Communication & Arts
English, History, & Humanities

College of Science, Technology, & Mathematics

At the LSUA College of Science, Technology, & Mathematics, students tackle complex problems through inquiry, innovation, and discovery. With immersive research opportunities, state-of-the-art labs, and dedicated mentorship, graduates can gain the knowledge and adaptability to excel in high-paying STEM careers.

Biological Sciences
Chemistry & Physics

College of Social Sciences

The LSUA College of Social Sciences develops leaders who are passionate about understanding people, communities, and society. Through applied learning, research, and real-world experiences, students are prepared to make a difference in fields that address today’s most pressing challenges.

Elizabeth M. Beard, Ph.D.

Provost & Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs

A native of central Louisiana, Elizabeth Milton Beard, Ph.D., graduated from Rapides High School (’92), earned her Bachelor of Arts in English and Secondary Education from Spring Hill College, and completed her master’s and doctoral degrees in English at Louisiana State University in Baton Rouge. Since joining LSUA’s English faculty in 2005, Beard has been a champion of student learning and faculty development. Beyond her academic work, Beard is deeply engaged in the community. She serves on the Board of Directors of the Alexandria Museum of Art and on the Generals Athletic Association Board, advancing both the cultural and educational missions of the region she proudly calls home.

Teaching with Excellence. Learning with Purpose.

Academic Units

The Pentagon of Engaged Teaching & Learning unites five academic branches into a comprehensive framework that enhances student learning, supports faculty development, and advances innovative teaching practices at LSUA. Together, these initiatives elevate LSUA’s academic programming and are fundamental to the success of both the university and its students.
